01:49:10.169 --> 01:49:11.878
And why is that, Steve?

01:49:11.962 --> 01:49:13.504
You're not giving a speech

01:49:13.589 --> 01:49:15.465
because the vice
presidential candidate

01:49:15.549 --> 01:49:19.177
has never given a concession
speech on election night.

01:49:19.261 --> 01:49:21.304
It's not about you.

01:49:21.388 --> 01:49:23.556
It's about the country.

01:49:23.640 --> 01:49:26.517
Yeah, well, there's a lot of
things never been done before.

01:49:28.771 --> 01:49:30.313
Governor...

01:49:30.397 --> 01:49:31.981
this country has just elected

01:49:32.066 --> 01:49:34.525
the first African-American
president

01:49:34.610 --> 01:49:37.028
in the history of its existence.

01:49:37.112 --> 01:49:38.571
And it is the concession speech

01:49:38.655 --> 01:49:40.156
that will legitimise
his succession

01:49:40.240 --> 01:49:42.241
as commander in chief.

01:49:42.326 --> 01:49:44.577
It is a serious and
solemn occasion,

01:49:44.661 --> 01:49:47.246
and John McCain, and
only John McCain,

01:49:47.331 --> 01:49:49.749
will be giving this sacred speech.

01:49:49.833 --> 01:49:51.751
This is how it has been done

01:49:51.835 --> 01:49:53.753
in every presidential election

01:49:53.837 --> 01:49:56.005
since the dawn of the republic,

01:49:56.090 --> 01:49:57.673
and you, Sarah Palin,

01:49:57.758 --> 01:49:59.592
will not change the importance

01:49:59.676 --> 01:50:03.471
of this proud American tradition.

01:50:15.234 --> 01:50:18.778
We fought... We fought
as hard as we could.

01:50:18.862 --> 01:50:20.488
And though we feel short,

01:50:20.572 --> 01:50:22.698
the fail... the failure is mine.

01:50:22.783 --> 01:50:24.992
Oh, geez, no...

01:50:25.077 --> 01:50:26.619
I don't feel that short, Mark.

01:50:26.703 --> 01:50:28.913
Fell short, boss.

01:50:28.997 --> 01:50:31.332
- Yeah, thanks.
